  "text": "A general conclusion from craniofacial studies in the foetal period is that an association exists between the development of the cranium and the body axis/cervical spine and between the cranium and the central and peripheral nervous systems (CNS/PNS). This is not surprising as studies on the early gastrulation in the embryonic period have shown an axial midline structure in the body, the primitive streak [CITATION_1] , which will later involve the notochord and the head formation. The rostral extent of the notochord appears in the posterior wall of the sella turcica [CITATION_2] .",
